   <concept id="FAR_6_101" class="- topic/topic concept/concept " xtrc="">
      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">6.101</ph> Policy.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body concept/conbody ">
         <ol id="d364e13" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d378e10">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  <xref href="https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title10-section3201&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                        format="html"
                        scope="external">10 U.S.C. 3201</xref>
                     
                   and <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title41-section3301&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                        scope="external"
                        format="html">41 U.S.C.3301</xref> require, with certain limited exceptions (see <xref href="Subpart_6.2.dita#FAR_Subpart_6_2"
                        base="i1119917"
                        outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                        class="- topic/xref ">subpart  6.2</xref> and <xref href="Subpart_6.3.dita#FAR_Subpart_6_3"
                        base="i1119434"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">6.3</xref>), that contracting officers shall promote and provide for full and open competition in soliciting offers and awarding Government contracts.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d378e26">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph> Contracting officers shall provide for full and open competition through use of the competitive procedure(s) contained in this subpart that are best suited to the circumstances of the contract action and consistent with the need to fulfill the Government’s requirements efficiently (
                     <xref href="https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title10-section3201&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                        format="html"
                        scope="external">10 U.S.C. 3201</xref>
                     
                   and <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title41-section3301&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                        scope="external"
                        format="html">41 U.S.C. 3301</xref>).</p>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
   </concept>
